    "answer_id" : 42616112,
    "question_id" : 11053144,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Configuration for <strong>IntelliJ IDEA CE 2016.3.4</strong> to enable JavaDocs on mouse hover. I am running IntelliJ IDEA on Mac OS but believe that Linux/Windows should have similar options.</p>\n<p><strong>Autopopup docs:</strong>\n<code>IntelliJ IDEA</code> &gt; <code>Preferences</code> &gt; <code>Editor</code> &gt; <code>General</code> &gt; <code>Code Completion</code></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/OEizD.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/OEizD.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n<p><strong>Documentation on mouse move:</strong>\n<code>IntelliJ IDEA</code> &gt; <code>Preferences</code> &gt; <code>Editor</code> &gt; <code>General</code></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/yS0NG.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/yS0NG.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n<p>NOTE: Please hit <strong>Apply</strong> button to apply these settings</p>\n"
  } ],
